## Limitations

This report is limited by the availability of historical records and the potential biases in historical documentation. The complexity of the transatlantic slave trade, involving numerous countries and spanning several centuries, means that some details may be oversimplified. Additionally, the perspectives of the African societies involved in the trade are less documented, which may lead to an incomplete understanding of their role and experiences.